	<div class="container content">
		<p>
			<strong>Who is Doug Cash?</strong><br />
			Doug is a Retail Roofing Business owner who needs a way to collect payment
			without waiting for the customer to send a check. The ideal workflow was
			collecting payment on completion of the final walk-through at the end of
			the project.
		</p>
	</div>
	<div class="container content bullet-group">
		<h3>Market research came next.</h3>
		<p>
			Based on our research, we developed more educated questions to help us
			further understand the best approach for designing a strong user
			experience:
		</p>
		<p>
			What are other applications doing to collect payment promptly? What are
			some roadblocks? What's working for them? What's not?
		</p>
		<h4>A couple of key points we discovered through our research:</h4>
		<li class="bullet">
			<span>&#10112;</span> There are a lot of card service providers that have
			found success doing similar things AccuPay is trying to accomplish.
		</li>
		<li>
			<span>&#10113;</span> The feeling of safety and security for our users
			needs to be a top priority, otherwise they will not feel comfortable using
			the app to complete transactions.
		</li>
		<li>
			<span>&#10114;</span> Users have little patience for similar apps that do
			not quickly and effectively behave as expected. A user will quit the app
			quickly if they become frustrated
		</li>
	</div>
